  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F. ",
    "In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, salt, and sugar. ",
    "Add the cold unsalted butter to the dry ingredients and use a pastry blender or your fingers to work it into the flour until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. ",
    "Add the beaten egg to the mixture and mix until the dough comes together in a ball. ",
    "Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes. ",
    "While the dough is chilling, prepare the filling by cooking the chopped onion, diced red bell pepper, minced garlic, sliced fennel, oregano, thyme, cumin, coriander, paprika, and salt in a large skillet over medium heat until the vegetables are softened. ",
    "Stir in the drained black beans, warm water, apple cider vinegar, and chopped bacon (if using). ",
    "Roll out the chilled dough on a lightly floured surface to a thickness of about 1/8 inch. ",
    "Transfer the dough to a 9-inch round ttukbaegi earthenware cookware or a regular baking dish. ",
    "Spread the bean filling evenly over the dough, leaving a 1-inch border around the edges. ",
    "Fold the edges of the dough up over the filling, pressing gently to seal. ",
    "Bake the Maillard-Flaky Brazilian Beans Bake for 35-40 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the filling is hot and bubbly. ",
    "Remove the bake from the oven and let it cool for 10 minutes before slicing and serving. ",
    "Garnish with chopped cilantro and shredded cheddar cheese (if using). ",
    "Serve warm and enjoy! ",
    "Optional: Top with a dollop of sour cream or a sprinkle of grated Parmesan cheese. "
  ],
